    <!-- SECTION 4: SALES PREMISE + OBJECTION HANDLING -->
    <div class="section">
      <div class="eyebrow">Sales Premise & Objection Handling</div>
      <div class="section-title">What you're really selling — and every "no" answered</div>
      <div class="section-sub">The premise is the foundation of every conversation. Internalize it first. Then use the objection responses to keep momentum when a partner pushes back.</div>

      <!-- PREMISE BOX -->
      <div class="premise-box">
        <div class="premise-label">The Core Premise</div>
        <div class="premise-statement">"We don't manufacture the village — we give the village a way to act. If someone loves your client, YourKitchen is how they show it."</div>
        <div class="premise-sub">You are not a meal delivery service. You are not a subscription app. You are a care platform that activates existing relationships at the exact moment a family needs support most. The org is not promising meals — they're offering access to a tool. That distinction matters in every sales conversation.</div>
      </div>

